Definition.WordDefinition: Teenage \Teen"age\, n. The longer wood for making or mending fences. [Prov. Eng.] --Halliwell. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Teenage \Teen"age`\ (t[=e]n"[=a]j), n. of or pertaining to a teenager; being in one's teens; as, a busload of teenage football fans; teenage inexperience. [PJC]
teenage adj : being of the age 13 through 19; "teenage mothers"; "the teen years" [syn: {adolescent}, {teen}, {teenaged}]
